text.section:
The court may:
affirm the decision of the district council;
remand the case for further proceedings; or
reverse or modify the decision if the substantial rights of the petitioner have been prejudiced because the district council's action is:
unconstitutional;
in excess of the statutory authority or jurisdiction of the district council;
made on unlawful procedure;
affected by other error of law;
unsupported by competent, material, and substantial evidence in view of the entire record as submitted; or
arbitrary or capricious.
